resources.string:
			RSP program is intended for remote control and protect your phone against loss or theft by sending sms messages relevant (command).

 Functions of the program:
 		1. The program works in the background;
 		2. Program at startup (restart) the phone keeps track replacement sim - card. If a replacement sim has been made on the phone - card, your contact that you have chosen as an extra protection, get a message with the last coordinates of the phone;
 		3. Remotely turn the sound;
 		4. Remote Locate Phone (include GPS);
 		5. Remotely check the status of the battery;
 		6. Remotely enable notification (playing music, running vibration, display and output to the appropriate message screen);
 		7. Remotely turn off the notification;
 		8. Viewing the received coordinates on google map;
9. Administration of ready commands to the program.

 Note:
 		1. For those who do not have the program and you will get a message: "Coordinates-xx.xxxxxxx, xx.xxxxxxx-x.xkm/h-gps(or network)-", copy the two long numbers and insert them in the Google maps on the spot "on the Google search maps". The number that stands in front of "km/h" shows how the speed of the machine is moving. The word that comes after "km/h" (gps or network) indicates the type of positioning device.
 				gps - this is the exact positioning by satellite;
 				network - positioning through the mobile operator or the Wi-Fi network.
 		2. The command dial can be manually and send via normal sms manager. The message must consist of a password in order to whom you send the command from the command itself. For example: "1234-onSound-", in 1234 - is the password, onSound- - a team.
 Teams:
 			onSound- - turn the sound;
 			onGPS- - include GPS;
 			onNotif- - enable notifications;
 			offNotif- - turn off the notification;
 			onBattery- - check the status of the battery.
 		3. In order for your phone to react to the "find out the location of the phone", be sure about the included "source of data on the location" in "Service position". Turn on or "the GPS satellites" or "location on the network";
 		4. Try to remember your own password. In the case of blackouts, send the following sms message: "My Question", and wait for the security question that you selected, and then type your answer to the security question in parenthesis and send. If the answer is correct, you will receive your forgotten password.

 Use of health.
